  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Internal Displacement Monitoring in Burundi through the Displacement Tracking Matrix</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Burundian Government and the international community need reliable and consistent information on the displaced population to plan and provide assistance. The objective of this project is to contribute to evidence-based information to assist communities affected by displacement towards durable solutions. Over the course of the 12-month project, IOM&apos;s Displacement Tracking Matrix is producing and disseminating 15 information products which will include 6 dashboards and 9 reports. Moreover, IOM is building and strengthening the capacity of the Burundian Red Cross in the field to undertake the assessments in a unified and systematized manner to provide reliable information on the current internally displaced persons situation and host community needs.</narrative>
  </description>
